# 🎓 Google ADK — Step-by-Step Learning Roadmap

A hands-on, progressive learning path from beginner → advanced agent builder.
Each level builds on the previous one. All exercises use your existing project setup.

---

## 🧠 Core Concepts: The Anatomy of Any AI Agent

Before diving into levels, understand the **5 pillars** every AI agent is built on:

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[🤖 AI Agent] --> B[🧾 Prompts]
    A --> C[🔧 Tools]
    A --> D[🧠 Memory]
    A --> E[🛡️ Guardrails]
    A --> F[🔀 Orchestration]
    B --> B1[System Prompt]
    B --> B2[Developer Prompt]
    B --> B3[User Prompt]
    C --> C1[Function Tools]
    C --> C2[API Tools]
    C --> C3[Built-in Tools]
    D --> D1[Short-term / Session]
    D --> D2[Long-term / Database]
    D --> D3[RAG / Knowledge Base]
    E --> E1[Input Filters]
    E --> E2[Output Filters]
    E --> E3[Tool Permissions]
    F --> F1[Single Agent]
    F --> F2[Multi-Agent Transfer]
    F --> F3[Workflow Pipelines]
```

| Pillar | What it does | Real-life analogy |
|---|---|---|
| **Prompts** | Define WHO the agent is and HOW it behaves | Job description + training manual |
| **Tools** | Give the agent abilities beyond text generation | A toolkit — calculator, phone, database |
| **Memory** | Let the agent remember past conversations | A notebook or filing cabinet |
| **Guardrails** | Prevent harmful, off-topic, or incorrect outputs | Security guard + quality inspector |
| **Orchestration** | Coordinate multiple agents working together | A manager delegating to team members |

